lg.o: 2. As soon’s I beheld her, \ My heart was full sore; \ The longer I saw her, \ I lov’d her the more.
I could hear my heart dunting,
5. She said in a hover, \ Sir, what are you for?
I said, my dear jewel, \ I pray you compose.
Leave off with your jesting, \ I’ll take it no more.
7. As you are a stranger, \ You should not propose \ To have me decoyed,
I never propos’d, \ To have you decoyed
And stand to the promise \ You gave me before.

h.o: I entreat you, come kiss me, &c.

lg.o: I entreat you, come kiss me,
I care not for you Sir,
